<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 27 at 4:00PM MDT until May 27 at 4:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 415 PM MDT
FOR SOUTH CENTRAL KIOWA AND NORTHEASTERN BENT COUNTIES...
At 400 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles north of
John Martin Reservoir, or 25 miles west of Lamar, moving northeast at
25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Neeoshe Reservoir, Neegronda Reservoir, Sweetwater Reservoir and
Queens Reservoir.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
